  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The fecal calprotectin assay is used widely for inflammatory bowel disease diagnosis and the
      assessment of the disease activity. Some adenoma patients have elevated fecal calprotectin
      level, which could mean the role of fecal calprotectin as a screening marker for colon
      adenoma. We will investigate the usefulness of fecal calprotectin as colon adenoma marker for
      screening in this study.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
